==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|globus|lang=la}}, {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|globe|lang=fro}} + {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|εἶδος||form, likeness|lang=grc}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} A [[spherical]] representation or [[projection]] of a [[sphere]] or [[ellipsoid]].
#: ''A '''globoid''' is always round.''
# Mathematical connotation of [[globe]].
#: ''Pictures of planets and moons are usually presented as '''globoids'''.''

====Synonyms====
* [[globe]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} Of, or pertaining to, a [[globe]]
#: ''It's presented in '''globoid''' form.''

